youric an interactive gateway to hamlet learning design and technology skip to main content skip to main navigation stanford university school of education learning design and technology home ma programs suse stanford search this site about ldt academics admissions our students faculty & research ldt home home our students master's projects youric an interactive gateway to hamlet youric an interactive gateway to hamlet project by ani almario chica ando ruhi vasanwala project year 2003 who is youric and why does the king of denmark wants you to find him an interactive software environment youric aims to equip 11th and 12th grade students with the vocabulary they need to read hamlet more efficiently and effectively through challenges and decision points students will learn key terminologies in the play as well as gain familiarity with the grammar and setting of this great tragedy not only is youric an effective tool of contextual and definitional vocabulary instruction it is also a highly motivational learning product visit project website our students student portfolios master's projects life after ldt gallery of master's projects 2011 2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005 2004 2003 2002 2001 2000 1999 stanford university school of education 485 lasuen mall stanford ca 94305 3096 tel 650 723 2109 copyright 2012 stanford university all rights reserved site map contact suse admissions helpsu maps & directions suse it axess academic calendar stanford bulletin office of the registrar edmail stanfordwho stanfordyou login connect with us connect with us on facebook connect with us on twitter connect with us on youtube connect with us on flickr website by lyudmila christie suse it
